> Bulgogi sauce has a sweet and smoky flavour, thanks to its mix of soy, garlic,
> brown sugar and pear & apple purees. Bulgogi is a perfect match for rice and
> noodle dishes or even as a flavour driver in tacos.

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, @Sliced Mushrooms{80%g},
@Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}, ~{5-6%mins}.

> Add less spice if you'd prefer things milder.

Break up the mince as it cooks.

Meanwhile, pour the hot water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Boil the @Egg Noodle Nest{125%g}, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.

Drain the fat from the beef.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment
after handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the @Bulgogi Sauce{75%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp}.

Add the noodles. Toss to coat.

Heat up, ~{1-2%mins}.

Taste and season if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if needed.

Share your bulgogi noodles between the #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g}.

Enjoy!